title: Myriam Hernandez - Invencible Usa Tour 2024
summary:
Get ready for 'Invencible Tour" by Myriam Hernandez! This Chilean music legend, known for her romantic ballads, has a career spanning over three decades. She's received numerous awards, including Best Latin Artist by ACE in 1997 and a Latin Grammy nomination in 2011 for "Seduccion14." In 2022, she made history by becoming the first female artist from Chile to win the Latin Grammy Award for Musical Excellence. Myriam recently released "Nos lo hemos Dicho Todo," showcasing her enduring passion for music. Don't miss her unforgettable live concert experience during "Invencible Tour." NO BAG POLICY. Exceptions will be made for bags smaller than 10" x 7" x 2". All bags are subject to inspection by our security team upon entry. Effective August 1st, 2024, the Box Office will become a cashless facility. We will only accept Mc, Visa, Amex and Discover with a proper photo ID. We apologize for any inconvenience.

title: Fiesta Flamenca
summary:
Ballet Flamenco La Rosa, an international Flamenco company based in Miami, is made up of musicians from Spain, the U.S. and Latin America, is pleased to announce its performance of Fiesta Flamenca.

Led by the world-renowned Ilisa Rosal, this production features the spellbinding and earthy power of Flamenco dance at its best. With its spectacular footwork, precise athleticism and vibrant energy, Flamenco is at once sensual and spiritual, raw and refined, and filled with both restrained passion and electrifying release, making it a powerful and passionate evening.

This production will incorporate live music, original choreography and improvisation by exceptional Flamenco artists. The music will be composed, arranged and performed live by Guitarist Rodrigo Valdez and Singer "El Cachito", creating an interchange with the choreography, danced by Maria Mercedes Perez, Sandra Bara, Carolina Torres and Pilar Fernandez, including spontaneous improvisations where each artist is free to showcase their own individual style. Flamenco’s vast potential to inspire, empower and engage, with the captivating energy created by the interaction between musicians and dancers makes for a unique and exciting dynamic that resonates with audiences throughout the world.

Food & beverage are available for purchase at the show. The Bandshell is an open-air covered venue, all programs are rain or shine. Your ticket, once purchased, is non-refundable. Any questions? info@miamibeachbandshell.com

title: The Downtown Mixer
summary:
**The Downtown Mixer: Weekly Networking Event for the Downtown Miami Community!**

A weekly series all about bringing together the vibrant and diverse community of downtown Miami for an evening of networking, connection, and fun.

Whether you're a seasoned professional, a new resident, or just love the downtown vibe, this is your chance to connect with fellow professionals, entrepreneurs, community leaders, and residents.

Enjoy happy hour from 7 PM to 9 PM, featuring some of our signature cocktails and a selection of house beer, wine, and spirits at happy hour prices.

We're also inviting community members who want to get involved in future editions to reach out. If you or your organization would like to host or participate in upcoming mixers, please email us at info@mode.miami.

RSVP now and enjoy a welcome drink from MODE as a token of our appreciation for making Downtown Miami such an exciting place to be.

title: Alcolirykoz
summary:
Alcolirykoz is rap in its purest form, noble artisans who found in the rhymes the way to resist the passage of the days and the ruthless rush of the street, accounting for the story in each letter, they are genuine children of the 80's when the only thing that could be done was to embolate with music the aggressive roars of a city in destruction, they are three artists born in a popular neighborhood, cradled since childhood by the inexhaustible sounds of suburban genres as diverse as soul, blues, salsa, boleros, funk and so many more that later became influences.

title: TWYN
summary:
Get ready for an electrifying night at MODE's Downtown Jazz Night on Tuesday, June 11th, featuring the innovative duo TWYN. This experimental pair, consisting of keyboardist Jason Matthews and drummer/singer Aaron Glueckauf, crafts a sound that bridges the gap between vintage and modern, blending indie-electronica, breakbeat, hip-hop, and funk into a seamless, dynamic performance.

Based in Miami, TWYN has spent over seven years producing and performing together, working on their projects like Electric Kif, The Politix, and Lemon City Trio, and touring internationally with renowned artists such as Cuban songstress Danay Suarez and guitarist Matt Schofield. Their deep-rooted synergy and cutting-edge production style result in a constantly evolving performance that pushes the boundaries of structured songwriting and instrumental improvisation.

Join us at MODE for an unforgettable evening as TWYN takes the stage, delivering a unique blend of rhythm and experimentation that responds to the energy of the audience. Begin your night with Happy Hour from 7 PM to 9 PM, and immerse yourself in the captivating sounds of TWYN starting at 9 PM. Whether you're a jazz enthusiast or simply in search of an extraordinary night out, this performance is not to be missed. Secure your spot now and experience the innovative spirit of TWYN live at MODE.
